{"tid":2167184,"cid":5,"subCid":10,"title":"[同共產黨冇分別］加州民主黨議員 提議收財產稅 話過去十年住過加州、淨資產>USD30M 就要俾淨資產既0.4%","createTime":"2020-08-21T02:32:17.000Z","updateTime":"2020-08-21T06:47:00.000Z","uid":48083,"like":1,"dislike":3,"uniUserReply":11,"replies":[{"pid":"602aa8c531e39181aa1c49b4a2f53d2ef5900e77","tid":2167184,"uid":48083,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-08-21T02:32:17.000Z","msg":"California Seeks Wealth Tax to Soak the Rich, Even Those Leaving<br />\nAug 19, 2020<br />\n<br />\nSoak the Rich Scheme<br />\n<strong><br />\nCalifornia legislators seek a Wealth Tax that applies to anyone who has lived in the state for the last 10 years.</strong><br />\n<br />\nA pack of Democratic lawmakers in California are proposing a wealth tax for the state's richest citizens, forcing them to pay more essentially just for owning a lot of stuff. <br />\n<br />\n&quot;The California Wealth Tax would add critically needed revenue for California by creating a more equitable tax structure,&quot; [assemblyman] Rob Bonta said in a press release promoting the bill. &quot;<br />\n<strong><span class=\"red\"><br />\nThe proposed wealth tax would add a .4 percent tax on a taxpayer's net worth for net worths that exceed $30 million, which Bonta estimates will affect fewer than 31,000 Californians. </span></strong>From this proposed wealth tax, he estimates the state will raise $7.5 billion per year. The state currently faces a $54 billion budget deficit due in part to economic downturns from the coronavirus pandemic.<br />\n<br />\nYou don't even need to ask whose bright idea this was because Bonta is actually quite happy to reveal that the bill's co-sponsors are the California Federation of Teachers, the California Teachers Association, and the Service Employees International Union.<br />\n<br />\nBlatant Theft<strong><span class=\"red\"><span class=\"large\"><br />\n<br />\nA wealth tax is blatant theft that would likely not stand a legal challenge. <br />\n</span></span></strong><br />\nYet,higher and higher taxes are exactly the kind of thing one can expect more of. <br />\n<br />\nIn states like California, Illinois, and New Jersey, the call for higher taxes will never stop. <br />\n<br />\nEven if a wealth tax is ruled unconstitutional, Bonta and his ilk will just seek higher and higher progressive rates on income.<br />\n<br />\n<a href=\"https://www.thestreet.com/mishtalk/economics/california-seeks-wealth-tax-to-soak-the-rich-even-those-leaving\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thestreet.com%2Fmishtalk%2Feconomics%2Fcalifornia-seeks-wealth-tax-to-soak-the-rich-even-those-leaving&d=fUB9jTkReJc3fMEQQRliu7tp0LkHB2EL0pKzUaHUqTQ%3D&h=a0d5e5f6\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.thestreet.com/mishtalk/economics/california-seeks-wealth-tax-to-soak-the-rich-even-those-leaving</a>"},{"pid":"e6cc67aeedc69692022a94a4c25a36c906f02751","tid":2167184,"uid":71237,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-08-21T02:43:16.000Z","msg":"民主黨州份稅"},{"pid":"28e67dfc51dbcab07566711d709417d130345589","tid":2167184,"uid":14918,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-08-21T02:44:31.000Z","msg":"應該無人理佢<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"e6699287afaad3ac0437e92dd95503c8e22b6404","tid":2167184,"uid":189404,"like":1,"dislike":0,"score":1,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-08-21T02:45:31.000Z","msg":"最驚你唔咁做"},{"pid":"09275e07c5815cd1e277adbc9f21ac099c10b34f","tid":2167184,"uid":3776,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-08-21T02:46:40.000Z","msg":"支持 民主黨率先交"},{"pid":"c3dd3d8ac984867debcd791fe5b6151dab6d395c","tid":2167184,"uid":45213,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-08-21T04:05:04.000Z","msg":"Hollywood班聖人快撚d磅水<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/smile.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"1bb4316614022df46a3aaeedea020327c7e8c247","tid":2167184,"uid":59832,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"202